---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="SpecFerret: Spec Drift Detection CLI for API Contracts"
  description="Detect API spec drift before production. SpecFerret CLI catches breaking changes in data contracts with pre-commit hooks."
>
  <main>
    <header class="topbar">
      <div class="brand mono">specferret.dev</div>
      <a class="repo" href="https://github.com/BenGardiner123/spec-ferret"
        >GitHub</a
      >
    </header>

    <section class="hero">
      <p class="pill mono">Open source CLI • npm: @specferret/cli</p>
      <h1>Catch spec drift before it breaks production.</h1>
      <p class="subhead">
        SpecFerret is a CLI that detects when API specs, contracts, and shipped
        behavior drift apart. Block risky commits with pre-commit checks and
        clear impact reports.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a
          class="cta primary"
          href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@specferret/cli">Install CLI</a
        >
        <a class="cta" href="https://github.com/BenGardiner123/spec-ferret"
          >Read the code</a
        >
      </div>
      <pre
        class="quick mono"><code>bun install -g @specferret/cli
ferret init
ferret lint</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="section why">
      <h2>Why SpecFerret</h2>
      <div class="proof-grid">
        <article>
          <h3>AI ships code quickly</h3>
          <p>
            LLM-assisted development accelerates changes, but specs are often
            left behind. SpecFerret catches that mismatch before deploy.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3>Breaking vs non-breaking</h3>
          <p>
            It classifies drift so teams do not panic over harmless optional
            additions but do block true consumer-breaking changes.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3>Commit-time enforcement</h3>
          <p>
            Pre-commit hooks fail fast and keep bad contract changes out of main
            branch and out of production.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section use-cases">
      <h2>Use Cases</h2>
      <div class="proof-grid">
        <article>
          <h3>API teams</h3>
          <p>
            Detect shape changes in request and response contracts before
            clients break in staging or prod.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3>Multi-team repos</h3>
          <p>
            Backend changes can impact many consumers. SpecFerret shows direct
            and transitive impact in one report.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3>AI-assisted workflows</h3>
          <p>
            Keep generated code and contract docs in sync when rapid edits land
            through agents or pair-programming loops.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <h3>TypeScript shape checks</h3>
          <p>
            Validate declared types against contract expectations to reduce
            drift between docs and runtime reality.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section how">
      <h2>How It Works</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <span class="mono">1.</span>
          Define contracts in markdown with frontmatter schema fields.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="mono">2.</span>
          Run <span class="mono">ferret lint</span> to detect drift and classify severity.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="mono">3.</span>
          Use <span class="mono">ferret review</span> to inspect downstream impact
          and resolve safely.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="proof-grid">
      <article>
        <h2>Deterministic checks</h2>
        <p>
          Run <span class="mono">ferret lint</span> locally and in CI with reproducible
          drift detection and clear failure output.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Contract-aware impact</h2>
        <p>
          Review mode reports direct and transitive affected contracts so teams
          know exactly what to update.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Production-ready publishing</h2>
        <p>
          Trusted publishing with OIDC from GitHub Actions, versioned releases
          on npm, and evidence-backed validation runs.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  main {
    max-width: 1080px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 1.25rem 1rem 4rem;
  }

  .topbar {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .brand {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .repo {
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.9rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    background: color-mix(in oklab, var(--paper) 90%, white);
  }

  .hero {
    background: var(--paper);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 1.6rem;
    box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(23, 32, 53, 0.08);
    animation: rise 550ms ease-out;
  }

  .pill {
    display: inline-block;
    margin: 0;
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--brand) 45%, var(--line));
    color: var(--brand);
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    background: var(--brand-ink);
  }

  h1 {
    margin: 0.8rem 0 0.6rem;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 7vw, 4.2rem);
    line-height: 0.95;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .subhead {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 48ch;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .quick {
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--brand) 35%, var(--line));
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 0.8rem;
    color: #1e2e45;
    background: #f6fff9;
    line-height: 1.5;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .section {
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    background: #ffffffbd;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 1rem;
    animation: rise 700ms ease-out;
  }

  .section h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.8rem;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }

  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 1.3rem;
  }

  .cta {
    text-decoration: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 0.72rem 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    background: #ffffffcf;
  }

  .cta.primary {
    background: var(--brand);
    color: white;
    border-color: var(--brand);
  }

  .proof-grid {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.8rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
  }

  article {
    background: #ffffffc9;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 1rem;
    animation: rise 650ms ease-out;
  }

  article h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  article h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.04rem;
  }

  article p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  ol {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }

  li {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.55rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 0.7rem 0.8rem;
    background: #fff;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .how .mono {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .use-cases h2,
  .why h2,
  .how h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.7rem;
    color: #15385a;
  }

  pre {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  @keyframes rise {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(12px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    main {
      padding-top: 0.9rem;
    }

    .hero {
      padding: 1.2rem;
    }

    .repo {
      font-size: 0.82rem;
    }
  }
</style>
